OPERCULUM ( Fig. 18 F–G ). Duplex, outer portion slightly concave; lamella of outer multispiral portion with 4.5 whorls, step-shaped; upper edge of lamella thin and projects slightly above fringe. Radula (
Fig. 18 H
). Rachidian with five cusps, central cusp approx. twice length of outer two on each side; first and second lateral teeth similar but second is slightly larger, each with four cusps and a vestigial fifth; first three cusps gradually increasing in size from centre outwards and fourth very small.

Known only from two forests, Nqadu approx. 20 km north of Mthatha and Bele to the north-west. Transkei Mistbelt Forest (
von Maltitz et al. 2003
), in leaf litter (
Fig. 16 A
).
